  "evidence_entities": [
    {
      "id": "PMC_UNKNOWN:abstract:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_UNKNOWN",
      "text_span_id": "abstract_1",
      "text": "Of all congenital adrenal hyperplasia (CAH), 95% to 99% is 21-hydroxylase deficiency (21OHD), an autosomal recessive disease.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "Review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC_UNKNOWN:abstract:2:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_UNKNOWN",
      "text_span_id": "abstract_2",
      "text": "21OHD is due to an insufficiency of 21-hydroxylase enzyme, which is encoded by the CYP21A2 gene and involved in cortisol and aldosterone production.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "Review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC_UNKNOWN:introduction:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_UNKNOWN",
      "text_span_id": "introduction_1",
      "text": "The predominant enzyme deficiency that accounts for 95% to 99% of all CAH cases is 21-hydroxylase deficiency (21OHD).",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "Review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC_UNKNOWN:introduction:2:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_UNKNOWN",
      "text_span_id": "introduction_2",
      "text": "The 21OH enzyme converts 17\u03b1-hydroxyprogesterone to 11-deoxycortisol and progesterone to deoxycorticosterone.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "Review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC_UNKNOWN:introduction:3:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_UNKNOWN",
      "text_span_id": "introduction_3",
      "text": "21OHD comprises 2 groups, the classic and nonclassic (NC) form. Classic 21OHD is further divided into salt-wasting (SW) (cortisol and aldosterone deficiency) and simple virilizing (SV) phenotype (cortisol and milder aldosterone deficiency).",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "Review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC_UNKNOWN:introduction:4:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_UNKNOWN",
      "text_span_id": "introduction_4",
      "text": "The main therapies in CAH are glucocorticoids to replace the deficiency and normalize the adrenal androgens and mineralocorticoids, compulsory in SW CAH but often also used in SV CAH.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "Review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC_UNKNOWN:introduction:5:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_UNKNOWN",
      "text_span_id": "introduction_5",
      "text": "Mineralocorticoids, in the form of fludrocortisone, are particularly important prior to and during pregnancy in patients with SW CAH but may also be used in those with SV CAH.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "Review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC_UNKNOWN:genetics:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_UNKNOWN",
      "text_span_id": "genetics_1",
      "text": "RCCX copy number variation (CNV), in the class III region of the major histocompatibility complex (MHC), is a complex, multiallelic and tandem CNV defined by the variation in the number of copies of a DNA segment covering 4 adjacent genes: the serine/threonine kinase 19 (STK19, also known as RP1), the complement 4 (C4), the steroid 21-hydroxylase (CYP21), and the tenascin-X (TNX) genes.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "Review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC_UNKNOWN:genetics:2:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_UNKNOWN",
      "text_span_id": "genetics_2",
      "text": "CYP21A2 (OMIM*613815), encoding the steroid 21OH enzyme, and CYP21A1P pseudogene involve 10 exons spanning 3.4 kb. These genes share 98% sequence homology in exons and around 96% sequence homology in introns.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "Review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC_UNKNOWN:genetics:3:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_UNKNOWN",
      "text_span_id": "genetics_3",
      "text": "Over 95% of deleterious variants leading to 21OHD are attributable to intergenic recombination events where microconversions, consisting in the transfer to CYP21A2 of deleterious variants usually present in the CYP21A1P pseudogene, represent 70% to 75%.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "Review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC_UNKNOWN:cahx:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_UNKNOWN",
      "text_span_id": "cahx_1",
      "text": "The genetic cause of CAH-X syndrome is a recombination event between TNXB and its pseudogene TNXA. The resulting 30 kb deletion includes the entire CYP21A2 gene sequence and part of the TNXB gene and produces a chimeric TNXA/TNXB gene (CAH-X chimera).",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "Review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC_UNKNOWN:cahx:2:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_UNKNOWN",
      "text_span_id": "cahx_2",
      "text": "The functional consequence of this rearrangement is the complete absence of the 21OH enzyme and the deficiency of tenascin-X, while the resulting phenotype is a hypermobility form of Ehlers-Danlos syndrome (EDS).",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "Review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC_UNKNOWN:diagnosis:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_UNKNOWN",
      "text_span_id": "diagnosis_1",
      "text": "To date, polymerase chain reaction (PCR)-based sequence analysis together with the multiplex ligation-dependent probe amplification (MLPA) test represents the best-practice genotyping able to respond to the diagnostic challenge.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "Review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC_UNKNOWN:prenatal:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_UNKNOWN",
      "text_span_id": "prenatal_1",
      "text": "Chorionic villus sampling (CVS), performed between 9 and 11 weeks of gestation, with molecular genotyping is currently the favored diagnostic method for prenatal diagnosis of CAH.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "Review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "PMC_UNKNOWN:prenatal:2:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "PMC_UNKNOWN",
      "text_span_id": "prenatal_2",
      "text": "Noninvasive prenatal diagnosis of CAH, which avoids risks related to amniocentesis and CVS, can be performed with fetal cell-free DNA (cff-DNA) that can be traced in the maternal circulation in the first weeks of gestation (fourth or fifth) before the completion of organogenesis.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "Review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    }
  ],
