  "notes": [
    "This review focuses on the genetics of 21-hydroxylase deficiency, the most common form of congenital adrenal hyperplasia",
    "The paper discusses complex genetic mechanisms including gene conversion, recombination events, and copy number variations in the RCCX region",
    "CAH-X syndrome represents a contiguous gene deletion syndrome affecting both CYP21A2 and TNXB genes",
    "Multiple diagnostic approaches are discussed including traditional PCR-based methods and newer techniques like cell-free DNA analysis"
  ]
